reviews.text: Good access (ramps to all platforms), clean, lots of amenities (including free water) and plenty of trains to a wide range of destinations. Used to travel to London several times and never had any issues.

Usually a good station, but platform misinformation tends to happen fairly often. The board indicates one platform number, may change at the last minute, and no one can actually help you other than repeat what’s on the board. Most of the times your train has already left and station assistants belatedly tell you “that was the train”. Not good enough.
It was big and beautiful station.
Good Railway station with frequent trains to London, Epsom, Redhill, Aldershot, Camberley, Ascot and Portsmouth

Not the best experience leaving Guildford Station. The train was cancelled due to problems on the line and we were told the replacement would stop at Clapham Junction- it didn't, just went straight through to Waterloo adding another 45 minutes to my journey. Otherwise the station itself is generally fine.
